{% comment %} object in liquid 

object is a data type that represents a collection of key-value pairs. 
An object can contain various types of data, including strings, numbers, arrays, and even other objects.
Objects are commonly used to represent complex data structures, such as products, customers, or orders in e-commerce platforms.
objects are defined using curly braces {} and key-value pairs are separated by commas.

syntax : 
        {% assign my_object = {"key1": "value1", "key2": "value2", "key3": "value3"} %}

object methods : 
        1. object.keys
        2. object.values
        3. object.size
        4. object.merge
        5. object.delete
        6. object.has_key?
        7. object.to_json
        8. object.to_yaml
        9. object.each
        10. object.each_key
        11. object.each_value
        12. object.sort_by_key
        13. object.sort_by_value

{% endcomment %}

{% assign my_object = {"name": "John", "age": 30, "city": "New York"} %}
{{ my_object.name }} <br>
{{ my_object.age }} <br>
{{ my_object.city }} <br>

